class SPADE(tf.keras.layers.Layer):
    def __init__(self, filters, **kwargs):
        super(SPADE, self).__init__(**kwargs)
        
        self.conv1 = tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters, kernel_size=3, strides=1, padding='same')
        self.conv2 = tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters, kernel_size=3, strides=1, padding='same')
        self.conv3 = tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters, kernel_size=3, strides=1, padding='same')
        self.batch = tf.keras.layers.BatchNormalization()
        self.gamma = tf.keras.layers.Multiply()
        self.betas = tf.keras.layers.Add()
        
    def call(self, inputs):
        t = inputs[0] # Target
        x = inputs[1] # Predicted output
        
        t = self.conv1(t)
        g = self.conv2(t)
        b = self.conv3(t)
        
        x = self.batch(x)
        x = self.gamma([x, g])
        x = self.betas([x, b])
        
        return x

class SPADERB(tf.keras.layers.Layer):
    def __init__(self, filters, **kwargs):
        super(SPADERB, self).__init__()
        
        self.SPADE1 = SPADE(filters, **kwargs)
        self.SPADE2 = SPADE(filters, **kwargs)
        self.relu1  = tf.keras.layers.ReLU()
        self.relu2  = tf.keras.layers.ReLU()
        self.conv1  = tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters, kernel_size=3, strides=1, padding='same')
        self.conv2  = tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters, kernel_size=3, strides=1, padding='same')
        self.wise   = tf.keras.layers.Add()
        
    def call(self, inputs):
        t = inputs[0] # Target
        x = inputs[1] # Predicted output
        r = x # Residual
        
        x = self.SPADE1([t, x])
        x = self.relu1(x)
        x = self.conv1(x)
        x = self.SPADE2([t, x])
        x = self.relu2(x)
        x = self.conv2(x)
        x = self.wise([r, x])
        
        return x

    x = SPADERB(512, name='SPADE_residual_1')([tf.keras.layers.Resizing(32, 32)(target), x])
    
    x = tf.keras.layers.Conv2DTranspose(256, kernel_size=3, strides=2, padding='same', name='UpSample_2')(x)
    x = SPADERB(256, name='SPADE_residual_2')([tf.keras.layers.Resizing(64, 64)(target), x])
    
    x = tf.keras.layers.Conv2DTranspose(128, kernel_size=3, strides=2, padding='same', name='UpSample_3')(x)
    x = SPADERB(128, name='SPADE_residual_3')([tf.keras.layers.Resizing(128, 128)(target), x])

    x = SPADERB(64, name='SPADE_residual_4')([tf.keras.layers.Resizing(256, 256)(target), x])
    
    x = tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(3, kernel_size=3, strides=1, padding='same', name='logits_output')(x)
    
    return tf.keras.models.Model(inputs=[inputs, target], outputs=[x, tf.keras.activations.tanh(x)])
